{"lemma":"يَقُظٍ","slug":"يَقُظٍ","root":"#.ق.ظ","root_slug":"_-ق-ظ","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ق-ظ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n42489","","n42492","n42493"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8F%D8%B8%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be awake"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to awaken"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be wary, be alert, be vigilant"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of يَقِظَ (yaqiẓa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"awake","examples":[{"text":"وَتَحْسَبُهُمْ أَيْقَاظًا وَهُمْ رُقُودٌ","english":"And you think they are awake while they are sleeping"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wake up"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put into vigil or watch"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n42489","headword_ar":"يَقِظَ","root":"yqZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaquZa","text_ar":"يَقُظَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, K;) and in the Msb is added"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqaZa","text_ar":"يَقَظَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is strange; (TA;) [but this I do not find in my copy of the Msb;] inf. n. [of the first]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqaZN","text_ar":"يَقَظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqaZapN","text_ar":"يَقَظَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) or the latter is a simple subst., (S,) and [of the second]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqaAZapN","text_ar":"يَقَاظَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He waked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woke; did not sleep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was not sleeping."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  See also 5."}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n42492","headword_ar":"يَقْظٌ","root":"yqZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows, in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n42493","headword_ar":"يَقِظٌ","root":"yqZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqoZN","text_ar":"يَقْظٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqoZaAnN","text_ar":"يَقْظَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"awake: not sleeping:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the last has this signification; (S, Msb;) and its fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqoZaY","text_ar":"يَقْظَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, Msb, K:) the pl. (K, &c.) of the first (IB, Msb) and second, (IB,) or of the first only, for the second has no broken pl., because of the rareness of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEulN","text_ar":"فَعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the measure of an epithet, (Sb, TA,) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayoqaAZN","text_ar":"اَيْقَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, IB, Msb, K,) which is applied to women as well as to men; (O;) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yqZAn","text_ar":"يقظان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yiqaAZN","text_ar":"يِقَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IB;) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yqZY","text_ar":"يقظى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqaAZaY","text_ar":"يَقَاظَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  And the first (ISk, S, Msb) and ↓ second (ISk, S) (tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vigilant, wary, cautious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of preparation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having his attention roused:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having his attention much roused, very vigilant, and possessing knowledge and intelligence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk.) [In the TA, each of these two epithets is said to be after the manner of the rel. n.; but they are both part. ns. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqiZa","text_ar":"يَقِظَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tyq~Z","text_ar":"تيقّظ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfikori","text_ar":"الفِكْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN yaqoZaAnu","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ يَقْظَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutayaq~iZuhu","text_ar":"مُتَيَقِّظُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqiZuhu","text_ar":"يَقِظُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaquZuhu","text_ar":"يَقُظُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man vigilant in mind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a fulaAnN layaqiZN","text_ar":"اـِنَّ فُلَانٌ لَيَقِظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily such a one is vigilant; not dull, heavy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"listless;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light in head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","O","Msb","IB","Sb","TA","ISk","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}